2
00:01:09,605 --> 00:01:12,691
我说不出是什么使我爱上越南
Ican't say what made me fall in love with Vietnam.

3
00:01:14,735 --> 00:01:17,738
因为这的女人声音使人迷醉?
That a woman's voice can drug you?

4
00:01:17,905 --> 00:01:21,492
因为这的一切都很热情?
That everything is so intense -

5
00:01:22,743 --> 00:01:24,662
颜色
the colours,

6
00:01:24,828 --> 00:01:26,580
气味
the taste,

7
00:01:26,747 --> 00:01:28,749
甚至这儿的雨?
even the rain?

8
00:01:28,916 --> 00:01:31,752
这儿的雨可不像伦敦那可恶的雨
Nothing like the filthy rain in London.

9
00:01:39,468 --> 00:01:42,304
片名: 安静的美国人

10
00:01:42,930 --> 00:01:45,099
越南西贡,1952 人们说不管你寻求什么
They say whatever you're looking for

11
00:01:45,265 --> 00:01:47,935
你都能在这儿如愿以偿
you will find here.

12
00:01:48,060 --> 00:01:49,937
人们说来到越南
They say you come to Vietnam

13
00:01:50,104 --> 00:01:52,773
你能立刻明白很多事
and you understand a lot in a few minutes.

14
00:01:52,898 --> 00:01:57,820
剩下的你得自己去经历
But the rest has got to be lived.

15
00:01:57,987 --> 00:02:00,280
首先是气味 -
The smell, that's the first thing that hits you -

16
00:02:00,447 --> 00:02:03,951
预示着你用灵魂交换的一切
promising everything in exchange for your soul.

17
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:08,580
然后是热天气
And the heat.

18
00:02:08,747 --> 00:02:11,000
你的衣服马上变得不像样
Your shirt is straight away a rag.

19
00:02:11,166 --> 00:02:13,877
你会记不起自己的名字
You can hardly remember your name,

20
00:02:14,044 --> 00:02:16,714
或是你来这是逃避什么的
or what you came to escape from.

21
00:02:18,632 --> 00:02:21,385
不过在晚上,这儿凉风悉悉
But at night, there's a breeze.

22
00:02:21,552 --> 00:02:24,847
这的河美极了
The river is beautiful.

23
00:02:25,014 --> 00:02:28,267
没有战争,那些枪声只是烟花
You could be forgiven for thinking there was no war,

24
00:02:28,434 --> 00:02:30,811
这些自欺欺人的想法都会被谅解
that the gunshots were fireworks,

25
00:02:30,978 --> 00:02:33,355
只有享乐最重要
that only pleasure matters.

26
00:02:33,522 --> 00:02:36,567
抽斗鸦片
A pipe of opium,

27
00:02:36,734 --> 00:02:40,362
或抚摸那说爱你的女人
or the touch of a girl who might tell you she loves you.

28
00:02:44,533 --> 00:02:47,119
然而有些事还是发生了
And then something happens,

29
00:02:47,286 --> 00:02:49,204
你知道那会发生
as you knew it would,

30
00:02:49,371 --> 00:02:52,499
然后一切都改变了
and nothing can ever be the same again.

31
00:02:55,252 --> 00:02:57,296
福勒先生
Monsieur Fowler.

32
00:02:57,463 --> 00:02:59,506
感谢你亲自过来
Thank you for coming in.

33
00:02:59,673 --> 00:03:02,343
很抱歉这时候打挠你
I'm sorry to ask you at this hour.

34
00:03:03,677 --> 00:03:05,804
我知道的不比你多
I know about as much as you do.

35
00:03:05,971 --> 00:03:07,848
他是美国人,大约30岁
He's an American. He's about 30.

36
00:03:08,015 --> 00:03:10,059
他为经济援助团工作
He works for the Economic Aid Mission.

37
00:03:10,225 --> 00:03:12,144
我喜欢他
And I like him.

38
00:03:12,311 --> 00:03:15,272
他是个不错的小伙子,说真的
He's a very good chap. Serious.

39
00:03:15,439 --> 00:03:20,194
不像其他欧洲饭店里吵闹的混球
Not like those noisy bastards down at the Continental.

40
00:03:20,361 --> 00:03:22,446
他很安静
He's a quiet American.

41
00:03:22,613 --> 00:03:26,533
是的,一个非常安静的美国人
Yes. A very quiet American.

42
00:03:28,619 --> 00:03:31,288
他死了,是吗?
He's dead, isn't he?

43
00:03:32,956 --> 00:03:36,919
不是做贼心虚 我只是根据事实推测
Not guilty. I just put two and two together.

44
00:04:01,944 --> 00:04:04,446
他被刀捅死的
He was killed by a knife.

45
00:04:07,908 --> 00:04:10,327
你能辨认出他吗?
Can you identify him?

46
00:04:11,537 --> 00:04:12,913
是的
Yes.

47
00:04:13,580 --> 00:04:16,500
他是...我的朋友
He was... a friend.

48
00:04:18,002 --> 00:04:21,046
老实说我并不怎么为他悲哀
To tell you the truth, I'm not completely sorry.

49
00:04:21,213 --> 00:04:24,258
这些美国人给我们惹了不少麻烦
These Americans are causing a lot of trouble to us.

50
00:04:25,676 --> 00:04:28,595
不过这始终是凶杀案
But still, a murder is a murder.

51
00:04:28,762 --> 00:04:31,056
能提供什么线索吗?
Anything to help us?

52
00:04:32,850 --> 00:04:34,310
没有
No.

53
00:04:34,476 --> 00:04:36,520
一点线索也没
Nothing at all.

54
00:04:40,357 --> 00:04:42,109
那请吧
Please.

55
00:06:03,232 --> 00:06:05,275
派尔...
Pyle...

56
00:06:10,406 --> 00:06:12,241
他死了
est mort.

57
00:06:17,579 --> 00:06:20,040
被暗杀了
Assassinated.

58
00:06:24,378 --> 00:06:26,338
怎么死的?
How?

59
00:06:28,048 --> 00:06:29,883
被刀捅死的
He was stabbed.

60
00:06:42,980 --> 00:06:44,398
是的
Yes.

61
00:06:46,984 --> 00:06:49,570
他很爱我
He was in love with me.

62
00:06:51,030 --> 00:06:53,699
是的,的确
Yes. He was.

63
00:06:57,870 --> 00:06:59,913
我很抱歉,凤
I'm so sorry, Phuong.

64
00:07:03,667 --> 00:07:06,253
我回我妈那儿
I go to my mother's.

65
00:07:10,632 --> 00:07:12,635
我得静一静
I must think.

66
00:07:25,022 --> 00:07:27,191
我是在欧洲旅馆里见到派尔的 -
I met Pyle where you meet everybody -

67
00:07:27,358 --> 00:07:29,068
在那儿你能遇到很多人
at the Hotel Continental.

68
00:07:29,234 --> 00:07:32,029
我每天上午11点都会在那儿
I'm there every morning at 1 1. 00.

69
00:07:32,196 --> 00:07:36,492
我是英国人,我有去喝茶的习惯
I'm English. I have habits. I drink tea.

70
00:07:36,659 --> 00:07:39,662
我是个记者,所以听听小道消息
I'm a reporter, so I listen.

71
00:07:39,828 --> 00:07:45,626
我有个情人 我喜欢看着她和朋友走进饮料吧
I have a lover. I like to watch her arrive at the milk bar.

72
00:07:47,127 --> 00:07:49,254
我在那看到艾登.派尔
And there was Alden Pyle.

73
00:07:49,421 --> 00:07:51,799
看到他年青正直的脸
A face with no history and no problems.

74
00:07:51,965 --> 00:07:53,884
我们都曾有过这样一张脸
The face we all had once.

75
00:07:54,051 --> 00:07:56,178
- 我叫艾登.派尔 -我叫托马斯.福勒
- I'm Alden Pyle. - I'm Thomas Fowler.

76
00:07:56,345 --> 00:07:59,807
- 你是伦敦时报的 - 你知道很多嘛
- The London Times. - You've done your homework.

77
00:07:59,974 --> 00:08:01,642
我读过你的文章
I've read your articles.

78
00:08:01,809 --> 00:08:03,769
- 我能坐这吗? - 请
- May I join you? - Please.

79
00:08:03,936 --> 00:08:07,064
你来西贡做什么,派尔先生?
And what brings you to Saigon, Mr Pyle?

80
00:08:07,231 --> 00:08:10,234
我是经济援助团的 负责医疗方面
I'm with the Economic Aid Mission, on the medical side.

81
00:08:10,401 --> 00:08:15,072
眼疾.你知道沙眼吗? 这病在这很普遍,实事上很容易治
Eye disease. Do know trachoma? It's very common here. Very easy to treat.

82
00:08:15,239 --> 00:08:19,076
- 你住在旅店? - 只是顺便过来喝杯茶
- Are you staying at the hotel? - No. I just dropped by for tea.

83
00:08:19,243 --> 00:08:20,828
我要经过这去上班
On the way to the office.

84
00:08:20,995 --> 00:08:23,372
能见到你真是意外的好运
This is really a stroke of luck for me.

85
00:08:23,539 --> 00:08:25,499
你是少数几个...
You're one of the few correspondents

86
00:08:25,666 --> 00:08:28,711
能深入战场了解事实真相的通讯员之一
who goes out into the field to see what's happening.

87
00:08:28,877 --> 00:08:33,674
不再是了. 而且我不认为自己是通讯员
Not any more. Besides, I have never thought of myself as a correspondent.

88
00:08:33,841 --> 00:08:36,635
我只是个记者,我没有自己的观点
I'm just a reporter. I offer no point of view.

89
00:08:36,802 --> 00:08:39,263
我不采取行动 也不参与行动
I take no action. I don't get involved.

90
00:08:39,430 --> 00:08:41,181
我只是报道我所看到的
I just report what I see.

91
00:08:41,348 --> 00:08:45,352
- 但是你总有想法吧 - 就算想法也是一种行动.
- But you must have an opinion. - Even an opinion is a form of action.

92
00:08:45,519 --> 00:08:46,812
我还是...
Still, I'd appreciate...

93
00:08:46,979 --> 00:08:49,690
派尔渴望知道越南的一切
Pyle was hungry for everything I could tell him about Vietnam

94
00:08:49,857 --> 00:08:52,067
越南的独立战争
and her fight for independence.

95
00:08:52,234 --> 00:08:54,945
为什么法国人打了败仗?
Why were the French losing the war?

96
00:08:55,112 --> 00:08:57,239
为什么共产党赢了?
And why were the communists winning?

97
00:08:59,199 --> 00:09:01,452
然后他见到凤
Then he saw Phuong.

98
00:09:03,620 --> 00:09:07,166
我当时就该意识到对派尔这样的人而言
I should have realised how saving a country and saving a woman

99
00:09:07,333 --> 00:09:10,002
拯救一个女子和拯救一个国家一样重要
could be the same thing to someone like Pyle.

100
00:09:10,169 --> 00:09:12,671
我们得遏制共产主义
We've got to contain communism.

101
00:09:12,838 --> 00:09:14,965
我们能做到
What could be done, what should be done,

102
00:09:15,132 --> 00:09:17,718
他的思想,他读的书
what he thought, what he'd read.

103
00:09:17,885 --> 00:09:19,970
他使我记起
He made me remember there was a time

104
00:09:20,137 --> 00:09:22,181
曾经我也有远大抱负
when I had wanted to make a difference.

105
00:09:22,348 --> 00:09:25,476
- 就这么看着他们失去自由吗? - "自由" 是个西式词语
- T o watch liberty snuffed out? - "Liberty" is a western word.

106
00:09:25,643 --> 00:09:28,103
你认为越南人的自由是什么?
How do you define it for the Vietnamese?

107
00:09:28,228 --> 00:09:30,022
自由选择权
The freedom to choose.

108
00:09:30,189 --> 00:09:34,234
你给他们选择权 他们会投票选胡志明
OK, you give them that, they vote and they elect Ho Chi Minh.

109
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:36,904
事实往往比它看起来要复杂
Things are more complicated than they seem.

110
00:09:38,405 --> 00:09:40,532
- 那是什么? -手榴弹
- What was that? - A grenade.

111
00:09:42,034 --> 00:09:45,621
- 听上去像汽车逆火 - 在这呆一个星期,你就能听出不同来
- It sounded like a car backfiring. - A week here, you'll know the difference.

112
00:09:45,788 --> 00:09:48,040
见到你真的很高兴
It's been a genuine pleasure meeting you.

113
00:09:48,165 --> 00:09:51,001
- 也许我们能一起吃个饭 - 我很期待
- Maybe we could eat dinner. - I look forward to it.

114
00:09:51,168 --> 00:09:52,586
好极了
Great.

115
00:09:52,753 --> 00:09:54,046
早安
Good morning.

116
00:09:57,966 --> 00:10:00,928
早安,辛.有什么新闻吗?
Morning, Hinh. Anything new?

117
00:10:01,095 --> 00:10:04,473
腐败,造假...
Oh, corruption, mendacity...

118
00:10:04,598 --> 00:10:06,350
我说了"新"闻
I said new.

119
00:10:06,517 --> 00:10:08,310
有谣言说...
There is a rumour that the communists

120
00:10:08,477 --> 00:10:11,480
共产党计划要袭击北部的Phat Diem.
are planning an attack in the north, at Phat Diem.

121
00:10:11,647 --> 00:10:13,774
你的线人说的?
One of your contacts?

122
00:10:14,858 --> 00:10:16,902
是的,先生
Yes, sir.

123
00:10:18,529 --> 00:10:20,906
你的电报
And a telegram.

124
00:10:21,073 --> 00:10:23,158
- 伦敦办事处发来的 - 史达明先生
- From the London office. - Mr Stemins.

125
00:10:23,325 --> 00:10:26,996
他说报社回顾了外国办事处的情况
He says the paper has conducted a review of the foreign desk.

126
00:10:27,162 --> 00:10:29,289
他想要你回伦敦
He wants you based in London.

127
00:10:30,541 --> 00:10:33,002
天啊
Christ.

128
00:10:33,168 --> 00:10:35,379
我以为你喜欢伦敦,先生
I thought you liked London, sir.

129
00:10:35,546 --> 00:10:38,632
我是喜欢,但只是喜欢那个地理位置 不是该死的去那儿
I do, but I like it just where it is. I don't want to bloody go there.

130
00:10:38,799 --> 00:10:40,968
为什么? 办事处差事?
For what? A desk job?

131
00:10:41,093 --> 00:10:42,928
也许他们认为...
They probably think it's cheaper

132
00:10:43,053 --> 00:10:45,472
让通讯社覆盖越南会更便宜
to let the wire services cover Vietnam.

133
00:10:45,639 --> 00:10:47,766
我们一共交过几篇报道?
How many stories have we given them?

134
00:10:47,933 --> 00:10:49,601
今年内?
This year?

135
00:10:49,768 --> 00:10:52,104
- 是的 - 三篇
- Yes. - Three.

136
00:10:52,271 --> 00:10:54,356
噢,该死
Oh, shit.

137
00:11:08,620 --> 00:11:11,832
也许...我该去那儿
Maybe... I should go up there.

138
00:11:13,292 --> 00:11:17,129
- 哪儿,先生? - Phat Diem.
- Where, sir? - Phat Diem.

139
00:11:17,296 --> 00:11:21,550
那地方可不容易进 共产党正在攻打那儿
It's not an easy place to get into, with the communist attack.

140
00:11:21,717 --> 00:11:24,678
给史达明发个电报
Send a cable to Stemins.

141
00:11:24,845 --> 00:11:27,848
了解你目前的顾虑.句号
Understand your current concern. Stop.

142
00:11:28,015 --> 00:11:32,353
正在写一篇重要的报道.句号
Am working on a story of major proportions. Stop.

143
00:11:32,519 --> 00:11:37,191
要求留下直到写完.句号
Suggest I remain in Saigon until completed. Stop.

144
00:11:37,358 --> 00:11:39,401
福勒
Fowler.

145
00:11:39,568 --> 00:11:43,030
什么重要的报道,先生?
Which story is that, sir?

146
00:11:44,948 --> 00:11:47,451
我不知道
I don't know.

147
00:11:47,618 --> 00:11:52,665
但我知道你一定认得什么人 能把我弄进那地方
But I'm sure you know someone who can get me in there.

148
00:12:23,570 --> 00:12:26,323
今天是我们的周年纪念 你不记得了?
Today our anniversary. Did you forget?

149
00:12:26,490 --> 00:12:28,492
这么快就两年了?
Can it be two years already?

150
00:12:28,659 --> 00:12:31,370
- 是的 - 是的?
- Yes. - Yes?

151
00:12:31,537 --> 00:12:35,124
小心点.我老了,很脆弱
Be careful with me. I'm old and fragile.

152
00:12:36,125 --> 00:12:38,127
没那么老
Not so old.

153
00:12:40,879 --> 00:12:43,465
也没那么脆弱
Not so fragile.

154
00:12:51,432 --> 00:12:52,891
托马斯!
Tom!

155
00:12:53,058 --> 00:12:56,603
托马斯.
Thomas.

156
00:12:56,770 --> 00:12:58,897
- 你好 - 你好
- Hello. - Hello again.

157
00:12:59,064 --> 00:13:01,525
我和一些朋友一起 介意和我们一块吗?
I'm here with some friends. Care to join us?

158
00:13:01,692 --> 00:13:04,778
- 凤,这是派尔先生. - 艾登,请
- Phuong, this is Mr Pyle. - Alden, please.

159
00:13:06,363 --> 00:13:08,073
很高兴见到你

160
00:13:08,073 --> 00:13:11,076
请原谅我的法语说得不好

161
00:13:11,785 --> 00:13:14,705
认识乔.滕尼吗? 是美国公使馆的
You know Joe Tunney, from the American legation.

162
00:13:14,872 --> 00:13:18,000
是的,我认识乔 最近又颠覆了什么小国了吗?
Yes, I know Joe. Overthrown any small countries recently?

163
00:13:19,585 --> 00:13:22,463
- 福勒到处都有同谋 - 没错
- Fowler sees conspiracies everywhere. - That's for sure.

164
00:13:22,629 --> 00:13:25,591
共产党真的要攻打Phat Diem吗?
Is it true that the communists are attacking Phat Diem?

165
00:13:25,758 --> 00:13:29,219
我他妈怎么知道? 我们只报道胜利
How the fuck should I know? We only report victories.

166
00:13:29,386 --> 00:13:32,473
我们有队医疗小组 不被允许经过金边
One of our medical teams wasn't allowed past Phnom Penh.

167
00:13:32,640 --> 00:13:36,226
- 我正想去那儿呢 - 那是个天主教城镇,是吗?
- I was thinking of going up there. - It's a Catholic town, isn't it?

168
00:13:36,393 --> 00:13:40,147
- 你今晚有约会吗?
- You got a date tonight? - Bill...

169
00:13:40,314 --> 00:13:42,149
她每晚都有约会
She's got a date every night.

170
00:13:42,316 --> 00:13:45,819
你有你的女人了,我想要我的
You got your piece of ass. I want mine.

171
00:13:45,986 --> 00:13:51,116
派尔,小伙子们, 我们去500女孩之家吧
Pyle, fellas, let's go to the House of 500 Girls.

172
00:13:51,283 --> 00:13:52,826
不,谢了
Oh, no thanks.

173
00:13:52,993 --> 00:13:57,623
- 我本该带他们去吃饭 - 我们已在 Arc en Ciel订了位子
- I was planning on taking them to dinner. - We've already booked at the Arc en Ciel.

174
00:13:57,790 --> 00:14:01,085
那很好 你们在那吃
That's great. You go eat at the L'Arc en Ciel

175
00:14:01,251 --> 00:14:03,462
我在隔壁吃
and I'll get eaten next door.

176
00:14:03,629 --> 00:14:06,674
听上去不错 来吧,比尔
Sounds like a plan. Come on, Bill.

177
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:09,343
跟我走
Walk with me.

178
00:14:24,066 --> 00:14:25,985
看上去是个不错的年青人
Seems like a nice young man.

179
00:14:26,151 --> 00:14:30,656
- 他干什么的? - 医疗援助什么的
- What does he do? - Something with medical aid.

180
00:14:34,201 --> 00:14:38,914
你先去占张桌子 我去拯救我们的派尔先生
You go and get us a table and I'll go and rescue our Mr Pyle.

181
00:14:40,749 --> 00:14:41,834
谢谢
Thank you.

182
00:15:27,046 --> 00:15:29,923
我不进去,我只是送他来
I'm not staying. Just dropping him off.

183
00:15:36,138 --> 00:15:38,682
派尔,快过来
Pyle! Let's get out of here.

184
00:15:42,144 --> 00:15:44,605
抱着她
Put your arm around this one.

185
00:15:44,772 --> 00:15:47,858
他们以为你已经挑了个姑娘 就不会缠着你了
If they think you've chosen one, they'll let you go.

186
00:15:48,025 --> 00:15:50,319
抱着她
Put your arm around her.

187
00:15:53,113 --> 00:15:56,909
- 晚安,格里吉! - 谁最想要这钱?
- Night, Granger! - Who wants the money most?

188
00:16:11,465 --> 00:16:14,218
凤小姐,很抱歉让你久等
Miss Phuong, please forgive us for keeping you waiting.

189
00:16:14,385 --> 00:16:15,678
我原谅你
I forgive you.

190
00:16:15,844 --> 00:16:19,473
- 我们不得不看看比尔是不是到家了 - 家!
- We had to make sure Bill got home. - Home!

191
00:16:19,640 --> 00:16:21,850
- 30号? - 什么?
- Number 30? - Sorry?

192
00:16:22,017 --> 00:16:26,146
舞小姐的票 你买张票跳一支舞
Tickets for the taxi dancers. You buy a ticket for a dance.

193
00:16:26,313 --> 00:16:30,442
买张吧.也许我会陪你跳
Buy a ticket. Maybe I dance with you.

194
00:16:33,696 --> 00:16:35,698
给你
There you are.

195
00:16:37,574 --> 00:16:39,368
能请你吗?
Shall we?

196
00:17:33,339 --> 00:17:35,257
凤是个很美的名字
Phuong is a very beautiful name.

197
00:17:38,385 --> 00:17:40,012
是凤凰的意思
It mean phoenix.

198
00:17:42,681 --> 00:17:46,727
我以为是花的意思 就像你头上戴的
I thought it meant flower. Like the ones in your hair.

199
00:17:46,894 --> 00:17:49,229
你喜欢我的发式吗?
Do you like my hair?

200
00:17:49,396 --> 00:17:54,109
- 这是传统发式 - 很漂亮
- This is traditional style. - It's very nice.

201
00:17:54,276 --> 00:17:57,112
- 会说越南语吗? - 当然.考我吧
- Do you know Vietnamese? - Sure. Try me.

202
00:18:00,157 --> 00:18:03,410
你跳舞时不要带领舞伴

203
00:18:04,662 --> 00:18:06,330
不,我不会...
No. I don't...

204
00:18:06,497 --> 00:18:08,499
我只知道两个词
I only know two words.

205
00:18:14,755 --> 00:18:16,757
- 福勒先生 - 你好
- Mr Fowler. - Hello.

206
00:18:16,924 --> 00:18:19,385
- 我能坐下吗? - 当然
- May l? - Of course.

207
00:18:19,551 --> 00:18:21,428
谢谢
Thanks.

208
00:18:21,595 --> 00:18:24,348
好久不见了
Haven't seen you for a long time.

209
00:18:24,515 --> 00:18:26,892
- 我常不在这 - 是的
- I'm away a lot. - Yes.

210
00:18:31,689 --> 00:18:34,233
他是谁?你朋友?
Who's he? Your friend?

211
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:37,277
他叫派尔 他是美国经济使团的
His name is Pyle. He's with the American Economic Mission.

212
00:18:37,444 --> 00:18:39,989
他来自波斯顿,美国
He's from Boston. In America.

213
00:18:40,155 --> 00:18:42,116
他跳得很烂
He's a very bad dancer.

214
00:18:42,241 --> 00:18:43,784
是的
Yes.

215
00:18:49,540 --> 00:18:54,795
- 他结婚了吗? - 据我所知没有
- He is married? - Not that I know of, no.

216
00:18:56,714 --> 00:18:59,550
这是凤的姐姐 艾登.派尔
This is Phuong's sister. Alden Pyle.

217
00:18:59,675 --> 00:19:02,136
很高兴见到你
Very happy to meet you.

218
00:19:04,305 --> 00:19:06,974
你父亲是商人?
Your father is a business man?

219
00:19:07,891 --> 00:19:10,269
不,他是教授
No. He's a professor.

220
00:19:11,228 --> 00:19:13,814
我妹妹舞跳得很好,对吗?
My sister is very good dancer, yes?

221
00:19:13,981 --> 00:19:17,151
- 比我好多了 - 她是我唯一的妹妹
- She's too good for me. - She's my only sister.

222
00:19:19,361 --> 00:19:21,822
他很可爱,是美国人 还很有钱

223
00:19:22,031 --> 00:19:24,491
有时你和你所讨厌的法国人 一样那么粗俗

224
00:19:25,993 --> 00:19:28,287
你妹妹很漂亮
Your sister's a very pretty girl.

225
00:19:28,454 --> 00:19:32,624
我妹妹是西贡最漂亮的女孩
My sister is the most beautiful girl in Saigon.

226
00:19:32,791 --> 00:19:37,755
我绝对相信 福勒先生是个非常幸运的男人
I don't doubt that at all. Mr Fowler's a very lucky man.

227
00:19:38,464 --> 00:19:42,343
我父亲因为没有孙子非常难过
My father was very sad he had no grandchildren.

228
00:19:44,345 --> 00:19:46,305
想喝点什么吗?
Would you like a drink?

229
00:19:46,472 --> 00:19:48,265
不,谢谢
No. Thank you.

230
00:19:48,432 --> 00:19:51,060
我朋友在那儿
My friends.

231
00:19:51,226 --> 00:19:54,772
真高兴见到你 期望很快能再面
So pleased to have met you. I hope we meet again soon.

232
00:19:54,938 --> 00:19:57,941
- 也许你能安排一下 - 等我从北部回来吧
- Perhaps you could arrange. - When I get back from the north.

233
00:19:58,067 --> 00:20:00,027
你要去北部?
You are going north?

234
00:20:00,152 --> 00:20:01,320
是的
Yes.

235
00:20:03,489 --> 00:20:05,532
那你一定要和我及我妹妹吃午饭
Then you must come and have dinner

236
00:20:05,658 --> 00:20:09,203
当福勒先生不在时
with me and my sister when Mr Fowler is gone.

237
00:20:09,370 --> 00:20:13,165
- 让她高兴高兴 - 谢谢,我很想去
- To cheer her up. - Thank you. I'd like that very much.

238
00:20:19,630 --> 00:20:22,216
- 多好的女子 - 绝对的圣人
- What a nice woman. - Absolute saint.

239
00:20:22,341 --> 00:20:25,844
她以前在进出口办事处工作
She used to work in office. Import-export.

240
00:20:25,970 --> 00:20:28,263
- 真的吗? - 她会速记
- Really? - She knows shorthand.

241
00:20:28,430 --> 00:20:31,475
- 是吗? - 也许你那需要人
- Does she? - Maybe you need someone.

242
00:20:31,642 --> 00:20:34,561
也许能想想办法
Maybe we could work something out.

243
00:20:40,567 --> 00:20:43,654
请原谅我和凤小姐跳了那么多次舞
Please forgive me for dancing with Miss Phuong so many times.

244
00:20:43,821 --> 00:20:46,865
- 我喜欢看她跳舞 - 她跳得真好
- I like watching her dance. - She's a very good dancer.

245
00:20:47,032 --> 00:20:49,994
那是当然 她以前靠跳舞吃饭呢
She should be. She used to do it for a living.

246
00:20:51,662 --> 00:20:54,498
- 什么意思? - 她以前是舞小姐
- What do you mean? - She was a taxi dancer.

247
00:20:54,665 --> 00:20:57,459
舞女,就在 Arc en Ciel.
A hostess. Here at the Arc en Ciel.

248
00:20:58,544 --> 00:21:00,921
我以为你说她是来自好人家的
I thought you said she came from a good family.

249
00:21:01,088 --> 00:21:05,759
是啊,但他父亲死了 所以姐妹俩得自己讨生活
She did, but the father died so the sisters had to earn a living.

250
00:21:05,926 --> 00:21:08,887
- 噢,那太糟了 - 什么?
- Well, that's too bad. - What?

251
00:21:09,054 --> 00:21:11,932
那不是只比街上那些女子好一点点?
Isn't that just a step up from the girls across the street?

252
00:21:12,099 --> 00:21:15,978
天啊,不 我等了六个月才约到她
Good God, no. It took me six months to get her to go on a date.

253
00:21:20,441 --> 00:21:23,277
手榴弹
Grenade.

254
00:21:27,489 --> 00:21:29,867
- 那你结婚了吗? - 是的
- So are you married? - Yes, I am.

255
00:21:36,248 --> 00:21:37,875
但不是和她
But not to her.

256
00:22:17,706 --> 00:22:20,501
有件事我还没和你说
There's something I haven't told you.

257
00:22:22,753 --> 00:22:27,049
总部来了电报,叫我回伦敦
I got a telegram from the paper, asking me to go back to London.

258
00:22:29,093 --> 00:22:31,261
那你会走吗?
So will you go?

259
00:22:32,513 --> 00:22:34,390
我给他们回了电报
I've cabled them,

260
00:22:34,556 --> 00:22:37,476
请求让我留下,但是...
asking them to let me stay, but...

261
00:22:40,145 --> 00:22:42,648
如果他们不付我薪水
if they stop paying me,

262
00:22:42,815 --> 00:22:45,484
我不知道我们该怎么生活
I'm not sure how we'll live.

263
00:22:47,778 --> 00:22:50,239
我和你一起回伦敦
I come with you to London.

264
00:22:51,115 --> 00:22:53,117
如果可以我一定跟你结婚
I'd marry you if I could.

265
00:22:55,536 --> 00:22:58,747
- 你知道的这点 - 是的
- You know that. - Yes.

266
00:22:59,915 --> 00:23:02,668
我总是这么跟我姐姐说的
That's what I always tell my sister.

267
00:23:14,096 --> 00:23:17,349
你觉得你妻子肯离婚吗?
You think your wife will give divorce?

268
00:23:22,604 --> 00:23:24,064
我不知道
I doubt it.

269
00:23:35,200 --> 00:23:36,952
一切从什么时候开始改变的?
When did everything change?

270
00:23:38,912 --> 00:23:41,457
也许不是一朝一夕的事
Maybe there isn't one moment.

271
00:23:44,209 --> 00:23:47,171
招我回伦敦的电报?
The cable from London calling me home?

272
00:23:47,338 --> 00:23:50,341
或盯着他们一起跳舞?
Or watching them dancing together?

273
00:23:50,507 --> 00:23:53,844
或是接下来我和她之间的...
Or what followed between us, she and I,

274
00:23:54,011 --> 00:23:56,221
漫漫长夜?
through the long night?

275
00:24:04,021 --> 00:24:06,023
我从没勇敢过
I was never brave.

276
00:24:06,190 --> 00:24:10,069
但我还是去了北部
But there I was, heading north,

277
00:24:10,235 --> 00:24:12,905
失去凤的恐惧...
the fear of losing Phuong more terrifying

278
00:24:13,030 --> 00:24:15,574
要大过挨子弹的恐惧
than the fear of any bullet.

279
00:24:22,373 --> 00:24:26,502
共产党人4天前袭击了这里
The communists attacked four days ago.

280
00:24:26,669 --> 00:24:29,338
到昨天才被我们击退
We pushed them back only yesterday.

281
00:24:29,505 --> 00:24:32,758
我们认为还有300人在村里
We think there is 300 in this village.

282
00:24:34,510 --> 00:24:38,097
- 但你看不到他们 - 情况越来越糟了,是吗?
- But you will not see them. - It's getting worse, isn't it?

283
00:24:38,263 --> 00:24:40,641
你们还能维持多久?
How long can you keep going?

284
00:24:40,808 --> 00:24:42,726
几个月,也许
A few months, maybe.

285
00:24:42,893 --> 00:24:46,480
我的手下都在数着子弹打
My men are counting bullets.

286
00:25:25,019 --> 00:25:27,396
不,不!别开枪!
No, no! Don't shoot!

287
00:25:32,609 --> 00:25:34,278
你来这干嘛?
What the hell are you doing here?

288
00:25:34,445 --> 00:25:36,530
他们不让我的车开过金边
They wouldn't let my truck out of Phnom Penh

289
00:25:36,697 --> 00:25:39,241
我只好设法自个过来
so I figured I'd see what was going on for myself.

290
00:25:40,326 --> 00:25:43,037
你能活着来到这真是幸运
You're lucky to get here alive.

291
00:25:46,373 --> 00:25:49,585
我弄到船后事情就不难了 这不贵
It wasn't that hard after I hired a boat. It wasn't expensive.

292
00:25:49,752 --> 00:25:52,129
- 最后我干脆买下它 - 你疯了
- In the end I just bought it. - You are mad.

293
00:25:52,296 --> 00:25:53,505
- 我疯了? - 是的
- I'm mad? - Yes.

294
00:25:53,672 --> 00:25:55,716
你有没有看到谁得了沙眼?
Have you ever seen anyone with trachoma?

295
00:25:55,883 --> 00:25:59,136
- 是的,我想是的 - 想事不关己不是那么容易的
- Yes, I suppose I have. - It's not that easy to remain uninvolved.

296
00:26:00,804 --> 00:26:01,764
这边走
This way.

297
00:26:01,930 --> 00:26:04,808
''事不关己不是那么容易的 ''
"Not that easy to remain uninvolved. "

298
00:26:08,646 --> 00:26:11,690
我躲在打字机后太久了
I had hidden for so long behind a typewriter.

299
00:26:14,652 --> 00:26:20,032
我们在 Phat Diem所见所闻
What we found there, what we saw, in Phat Diem.

300
00:26:20,199 --> 00:26:22,576
那意味这什么?
What did that do?

301
00:26:24,286 --> 00:26:27,081
他的热诚,我的冷漠?
To his zeal, to my detachment?

302
00:26:28,374 --> 00:26:30,584
死人就事不关己了
The dead are not involved.

303
00:26:31,710 --> 00:26:34,380
死人没有热诚
The dead have no zeal.

304
00:26:34,505 --> 00:26:37,383
他们躺着等待
They are lying in wait.

305
00:26:37,549 --> 00:26:41,804
你看见他们,他们的惨状
You see them, all their tenderness,

306
00:26:42,805 --> 00:26:45,224
荤绕在你心头,挥之不去
and then they haunt you.

307
00:26:46,684 --> 00:26:50,479
- 共产党人干的? - 这不是法国士兵干的
- Communists? - This is not the work of French soldiers.

308
00:26:51,397 --> 00:26:54,066
这不合情理
It doesn't make sense.

309
00:26:54,233 --> 00:26:57,361
共产党人不杀平民
The communists don't kill townspeople.

310
00:26:57,528 --> 00:27:01,991
- 他们犯不着这样 - 也许是另一个党派干的
- It is not in their interest. - Maybe another faction.

311
00:27:02,157 --> 00:27:04,243
这有那么多党派
There are so many of them.

312
00:27:05,202 --> 00:27:07,538
每个党派都有自己的军队
Each with their own army.

313
00:27:20,092 --> 00:27:22,136
你总在看的那本是什么书?
What's that book you're always reading?

314
00:27:22,303 --> 00:27:24,972
约克.哈丁 民主的威胁
York Harding. The Dangers To Democracy.

315
00:27:25,139 --> 00:27:27,725
- 美国作家? - 是的
- An American? - Yeah.

316
00:27:27,891 --> 00:27:30,269
他在这儿呆了几年才回去
He was out here a couple of years back.

317
00:27:30,436 --> 00:27:32,896
- 他呆了很久吗? - 我不知道
- Was he here long? - I don't know.

318
00:27:33,063 --> 00:27:35,566
我听过他的一次演讲 乔见过他
I heard him lecture once. Joe actually met him.

319
00:27:35,733 --> 00:27:38,610
他提出由第三方力量来控制越南
He put forward the idea of a third force to run Vietnam.

320
00:27:38,777 --> 00:27:41,947
- 不是共产党,不是法国人 - 不是美国人?
- Not the communists and not the French. - Not the Americans?

321
00:27:42,114 --> 00:27:44,408
不,我们可不是殖民主义者
No. We're not colonialists.

322
00:27:44,575 --> 00:27:47,119
有时那反而能真得帮助这些人
Something that could really help these people.

323
00:27:47,286 --> 00:27:50,706
- 你们谁有枪吗? - 没有
- You have a gun, either of you? - No.

324
00:27:50,873 --> 00:27:53,375
他们今晚会进攻这里
They shall attack again tonight.

325
00:27:53,542 --> 00:27:55,919
你不会想被活捉的
You don't want to be taken alive.

326
00:27:56,086 --> 00:27:58,213
相信我
Believe me.

327
00:27:59,548 --> 00:28:01,550
必要时自行了断吧
Shoot yourselves.

328
00:28:02,509 --> 00:28:04,303
- 谢谢
- Thank you. - Thanks.

329
00:28:04,470 --> 00:28:07,056
呆在碉堡里
Stay inside that bunker.

330
00:28:21,904 --> 00:28:24,907
- 想吃点吗? - 不,谢谢
- Do you want something to eat? - No, thank you.

331
00:28:26,742 --> 00:28:29,286
说吧
Come on.

332
00:28:29,453 --> 00:28:32,289
你来这不是为了医疗队
You didn't come up to check your medical team.

333
00:28:32,956 --> 00:28:36,543
乔.滕尼派你来的,是不是? 收信点情报
Joe Tunney sent you, right? A little intelligence work.

334
00:28:42,091 --> 00:28:45,427
我总是藏不住秘密
I've never have been very good at keeping secrets.

335
00:28:45,594 --> 00:28:49,139
我来这还有个原因
There is another reason why I came up here.

336
00:28:52,393 --> 00:28:55,562
- 为了你 - 我?
- It's you. - Me?

337
00:28:57,231 --> 00:28:58,565
是的
Yeah.

338
00:29:00,317 --> 00:29:02,987
你说过你可能来这儿
You said that you might be coming up here.

339
00:29:13,622 --> 00:29:15,249
我想说的是, 有关凤的
The thing is, it's about Phuong.

340
00:29:17,084 --> 00:29:20,004
呃,从那晚我们第一次见面
Well, I guess it started that night when we were

341
00:29:20,170 --> 00:29:22,506
在 Arc en Ciel,我和她跳舞
at the Arc en Ciel and I was dancing with her.

342
00:29:23,257 --> 00:29:25,759
我不认为你们会有近一步关系
I didn't think you ever got close enough.

343
00:29:25,926 --> 00:29:29,346
然后我和她还有她姐姐一起吃饭
And then I had dinner with her and her sister

344
00:29:31,432 --> 00:29:33,600
那个周六...
that Saturday and...

345
00:29:35,311 --> 00:29:39,356
当我坐在那儿看着她
just when I was sitting there looking at her,

346
00:29:40,899 --> 00:29:42,901
一切在我看来都再清楚不过了
it all just became so clear to me.

347
00:29:43,068 --> 00:29:45,279
我明白
I see.

348
00:29:45,446 --> 00:29:47,740
听着,托马斯, 我不是有预谋这样的
Look, Tom, none of this was planned.

349
00:29:47,906 --> 00:29:49,742
不可能...
There's no way...

350
00:29:49,908 --> 00:29:54,163
我从不相信一见钟情
I never ever used to believe in love at first sight.

351
00:29:54,747 --> 00:29:57,207
但是自从见到那可怕的地方的那些女子
But after seeing those other girls in that awful place

352
00:29:57,374 --> 00:30:01,045
并且想到凤很可能变成她们中的一个
and thinking that Phuong could easily become one of them,

353
00:30:02,212 --> 00:30:03,672
我想保护她
I want to protect her.

354
00:30:03,839 --> 00:30:06,550
你想保护她时她怎么说?
What did she say when you offered her your protection?

355
00:30:06,717 --> 00:30:08,886
- 我还没告诉她 - 你还没?
- I haven't told her yet. - You haven't?

356
00:30:09,053 --> 00:30:12,264
没.我觉得那样不妥 我想先告诉你
No. I didn't think it would be right. I wanted to speak with you first.

357
00:30:14,600 --> 00:30:18,354
听着,如果你们俩结婚了,那情况会完全不同
Look, if you two were married that would be completely different.

358
00:30:18,520 --> 00:30:20,773
我不可能和她结婚 噢,该死!
I can never marry her. Oh, shit!

359
00:30:20,939 --> 00:30:24,026
我妻子不可能同意离婚 她是天主教徒
My wife would never give me a divorce. She's a Catholic.

360
00:30:28,197 --> 00:30:31,659
他们靠近了,他们开进来了
They're getting closer. They're walking in.

361
00:30:54,765 --> 00:30:58,519
亲爱的托马斯 我想我会比你早回西贡
Dear Thomas - I guess I'll be back in Saigon ahead of you.

362
00:30:58,686 --> 00:31:02,231
我再次向你保证
And I wanted to reassure you

363
00:31:02,398 --> 00:31:06,110
直到你回来,我不会见凤
that I won't go to see Phuong until after you return.

364
00:31:06,276 --> 00:31:10,572
如果你能赶上下一次出城 你将会在这周末回来
If you can make the next transport out, you should be back by the end of the week.

365
00:31:11,782 --> 00:31:14,994
我会向你的助手打听你的消息
I can check in with your assistant to see if you made it.

366
00:31:15,160 --> 00:31:19,248
如果你赶上了,我会在周五来见你
If so, I'll come around to see you both together on Friday.

367
00:31:19,415 --> 00:31:21,375
 5.00行吗?
Say 5. 00?

368
00:31:22,459 --> 00:31:24,253
有人要去香港吗?
Anyone due to go out to Hong Kong?

369
00:31:24,420 --> 00:31:26,839
我想路透社的人会去
Someone from Reuters, I believe.

370
00:31:27,006 --> 00:31:29,883
把这个打出来,叫他帮我发到伦敦去
Type this up and ask him to cable it to London for me.

371
00:31:30,050 --> 00:31:31,969
- 你的大新闻? - 是的
- Your big story? - Yes.

372
00:31:32,136 --> 00:31:35,556
Phat Diem大屠杀 不知道谁干的
Massacre at Phat Diem. Nobody did it, of course.

373
00:31:35,723 --> 00:31:37,975
不是法国人,不是共产党...
Not the French, not the communists...

374
00:31:38,892 --> 00:31:40,728
只有各种谣传
But there are rumours.

375
00:31:42,938 --> 00:31:45,607
- 怎么回事? - 我忘了这事了
- What's going on? - I forgot.

376
00:31:45,733 --> 00:31:47,943
- 什么? - 是个集会
- What? - It's a rally.

377
00:31:48,110 --> 00:31:51,363
- 一个新的政党 - 真见鬼
- A new political party. - Bloody hell.

378
00:31:51,530 --> 00:31:55,367
我想还是把车留在这儿吧,先生 我们可以步行回去
I think I'd better leave your car here, sir. We can walk.

379
00:32:30,235 --> 00:32:33,697
- 那不是泰上校吗? - 是将军
- lsn't that Colonel The? - General The.

380
00:32:33,864 --> 00:32:35,783
- 谁升他为将军的? - 他自己
- Who made him a general? - He did.

381
00:32:35,949 --> 00:32:39,244
他脱离法国人,自己组建了军队
He broke away from the French and formed his own army.

382
00:33:14,905 --> 00:33:16,907
- 你好 - 嗨
- Hello. - Hi.

383
00:33:18,951 --> 00:33:20,953
你有狗
You have a dog.

384
00:33:22,955 --> 00:33:25,082
- 进来 - 谢谢
- Come in. - Thanks.

385
00:33:32,131 --> 00:33:35,259
- 凤在哪? - 她去看她姐了
- Where's Phuong? - She's gone to see her sister.

386
00:33:38,595 --> 00:33:41,849
- 想喝点威士忌吗? - 苏打水就行了,谢谢
- Would you like a whisky? - Just a soda, thanks.

387
00:33:45,519 --> 00:33:47,730
他非得跳上床吗?
Does he have to do that?

388
00:33:48,230 --> 00:33:50,607
公爵!到这儿来
Duke! Come here.

389
00:33:51,483 --> 00:33:53,277
- 你叫他公爵? -  是的
- You called him Duke. - Yeah.

390
00:33:53,444 --> 00:33:56,113
我在街上捡回来的
I found this guy in the street.

391
00:33:56,238 --> 00:34:00,117
谁会不理睬这么可爱的狗呢?
Didn't l? Who could turn their back on a mug like that?

392
00:34:00,951 --> 00:34:03,620
我在游行上看到你和乔.滕尼
I saw you and Joe Tunney at the parade.

393
00:34:04,455 --> 00:34:05,873
你也去了集会?
Did you go on to the rally?

394
00:34:06,040 --> 00:34:09,626
谢谢.是的,我去了 不过是为了别的事
Thanks. Yeah, I did. It was really something else.

395
00:34:09,793 --> 00:34:13,047
我以为只有美国政客才爱搞那种无聊事
I thought only American politicians went in for that nonsense.

396
00:34:13,213 --> 00:34:15,132
就差用来表示欢迎的彩带了
All that was missing was the ticker tape.

397
00:34:15,299 --> 00:34:17,968
他们没忘军乐队伴奏
They sure didn't forget the brass band.

398
00:34:19,011 --> 00:34:20,888
令人印象很深刻,那个泰将军
Impressive guy, that General The.

399
00:34:21,055 --> 00:34:23,724
你不介意他是个彻头彻尾的自大狂吗?
It doesn't trouble you that he's a complete egomaniac?

400
00:34:23,849 --> 00:34:28,062
听着,我不想在凤背后说她
Look, I don't want to talk about Phuong behind her back.

401
00:34:28,228 --> 00:34:31,065
我以为她会在这儿,但...
I thought she was going to be here, but...

402
00:34:31,231 --> 00:34:34,860
- 她姐姐跟我说了她的困境 - 什么困境?
- Her sister told me about her predicament. - And what predicament is that?

403
00:34:35,527 --> 00:34:37,404
我以为你知道
I think you know.

404
00:34:37,571 --> 00:34:39,490
你不能娶她
You can't marry her,

405
00:34:39,657 --> 00:34:43,702
和你在一起,她永远不可能与越南人有正常的婚姻
and by living with you she can never have a proper marriage to a Vietnamese man.

406
00:34:43,869 --> 00:34:46,914
她不需要同越南人有正常的婚姻
She doesn't need a proper marriage with a Vietnamese man.

407
00:34:47,081 --> 00:34:49,458
她和我在一起
She's with me.

408
00:34:49,625 --> 00:34:51,585
她来了
Here she is.

409
00:34:52,961 --> 00:34:54,463
你好,凤
Hello, Phuong.

410
00:34:54,630 --> 00:34:56,882
我姐出去了
My sister is out.

411
00:34:58,050 --> 00:35:00,636
- 你好 - 你好,很高兴见到你
- Hello. - Hello. It's nice to see you.

412
00:35:00,803 --> 00:35:04,974
派尔先生是特地来看你的,凤
It's you that Mr Pyle has come to visit, Phuong.

413
00:35:05,140 --> 00:35:06,976
为什么我们不坐下呢?
So why don't we all sit down?

414
00:35:07,142 --> 00:35:09,395
除非你想我离开
Unless, of course, you want me to leave.

415
00:35:09,561 --> 00:35:11,480
不,那不妥
No. That wouldn't be right.

416
00:35:12,773 --> 00:35:14,817
那我们坐下吧
We should sit down, then.

417
00:35:25,285 --> 00:35:27,454
说吧
Fire away.

418
00:35:35,587 --> 00:35:41,093
自从我见到你,同你跳舞,和你聊天
Ever since I met you and danced with you and talked with you,

419
00:35:42,553 --> 00:35:46,598
我无时无刻不想着你
I haven't been able to get you out of my thoughts for more than a moment.

420
00:35:53,272 --> 00:35:55,441
我已经爱上你了
I've fallen in love with you.

421
00:36:01,572 --> 00:36:03,324
你爱上我?
You fall in love with me?

422
00:36:03,449 --> 00:36:07,202
请相信我 我以前从没这样过
Please believe me. I've never behaved like this before.

423
00:36:07,369 --> 00:36:12,416
我很抱歉,这很唐突,不太礼貌,但...
I apologise. It is abrupt and it is ill-mannered, but...

424
00:36:14,877 --> 00:36:16,879
我爱你
I'm in love with you.

425
00:36:19,631 --> 00:36:21,675
你不该是单膝下跪的吗?
Shouldn't you be on one knee?

426
00:36:26,013 --> 00:36:28,766
凤,我不是个富有的人
Look... Phuong, I'm not a rich man

427
00:36:28,932 --> 00:36:30,392
但我有我的资产
but I do have assets.

428
00:36:30,559 --> 00:36:32,811
-我们来丢硬币决定吧 - 你能给她什么?
- Let's toss for her. - What can you offer her?

429
00:36:32,978 --> 00:36:36,690
- 噢,主啊 - 我不奢望你立刻爱上我
- Oh, Christ. - I don't expect you to love me right away.

430
00:36:36,815 --> 00:36:39,193
你总是和司机上床
You could always make love to the chauffeur.

431
00:36:39,360 --> 00:36:41,862
你没有权利侮辱她!
You have no right to insult her!

432
00:36:42,029 --> 00:36:44,448
- 让你那该死的狗闭上嘴 - 跟我走吧
- Shut your bloody dog up. - Come away with me.

433
00:36:44,615 --> 00:36:47,576
叫他走,带上他的狗
Tell him to bugger off and take his dog with him.

434
00:36:51,038 --> 00:36:52,414
不
No.

435
00:36:56,585 --> 00:36:59,171
你说不?
Did you say no?

436
00:36:59,296 --> 00:37:02,508
坐下喝几杯吧
Yes. Sit down and have a scotch.

437
00:37:02,675 --> 00:37:05,010
不,我该走了,我很抱歉
No. I should go. I'm so sorry.

438
00:37:05,177 --> 00:37:07,763
- 你想抽烟斗吗? - 烟斗?
- Do you want to smoke a pipe? - A pipe?

439
00:37:07,930 --> 00:37:09,848
鸦片
Opium.

440
00:37:10,015 --> 00:37:12,518
不,我干嘛要抽那个?
No. Why would I do that?

441
00:37:31,745 --> 00:37:34,081
我知道我们结婚前你就警告过我
I know before we married you warned me

442
00:37:34,206 --> 00:37:37,918
你的信仰决定了你不可能和我离婚
beliefs meant that there could never be a divorce.

443
00:37:38,085 --> 00:37:42,214
但我还是想请求你
All the same, that's what I'm asking for now.

444
00:37:42,381 --> 00:37:45,759
事实上,我深深地爱着另一个人
The fact is, I love someone very much.

445
00:37:46,969 --> 00:37:50,389
我期望你好好想想再答复我
I want you to feel affection and act before you have time to think.

446
00:37:50,556 --> 00:37:54,560
发电报告诉我你同意吧
Just cable and tell me you agree.

447
00:38:01,859 --> 00:38:05,779
我刚写信请求我妻子和我离婚
I've just asked my wife for a divorce.

448
00:38:10,993 --> 00:38:12,995
你姐姐...
Your sister...

449
00:38:15,748 --> 00:38:17,374
她真的不在?
Was she really out?

450
00:38:18,208 --> 00:38:20,210
我说了她不在
I told you.

451
00:38:23,714 --> 00:38:26,675
我以为也许她叫你回来
I thought perhaps she sent you back

452
00:38:27,468 --> 00:38:29,511
这样你就可以遇见派尔
so that you could meet Pyle.

453
00:38:30,262 --> 00:38:32,264
他是那么年青
He's very young.

454
00:38:34,933 --> 00:38:36,935
那并不重要
That's not so important.

455
00:38:48,030 --> 00:38:51,992
好消息.他们登了你的报道
Good news. They printed your story.

456
00:38:52,910 --> 00:38:57,081
我收到史达明的电报 他们让我再留一个月
I got a cable from Stemins. This got me a month's reprieve.

457
00:38:58,624 --> 00:39:01,835
第十页 ''法军突破共军包围.''
Page ten. "French Break Communist Siege."

458
00:39:03,837 --> 00:39:06,340
他们没全用我的报道,不是吗?
They didn't use much, did they?

459
00:39:07,508 --> 00:39:10,052
根本没提到村民被杀
Nothing here about the villagers that were killed.

460
00:39:10,219 --> 00:39:11,971
法国报纸怎么说?
What did the French papers say?

461
00:39:12,137 --> 00:39:15,474
头条当然是谴责共军
Headlines blame it on the communists, of course.

462
00:39:15,641 --> 00:39:18,686
好吧,一个月就一个月
Well, a month is a month.

463
00:39:18,852 --> 00:39:23,315
你还能告诉我什么有关这个泰将军的?
What else can you tell me about this General The?

464
00:39:25,067 --> 00:39:28,779
他既反对法军,也反对共军
He's set himself up against both the French and the communists.

465
00:39:31,448 --> 00:39:34,743
你认为他会接受我的采访吗?
Do you think he'd give me an interview if I went up there?

466
00:39:34,910 --> 00:39:36,662
很难说
Difficult to say.

467
00:39:36,829 --> 00:39:40,249
也许他认为他能有机会散布他的主张
Perhaps if he thought he could get his message across.

468
00:39:40,374 --> 00:39:43,085
问题是怎么通过关卡
The problem would be getting it past the censor.

469
00:39:43,210 --> 00:39:46,213
不,真正的问题是怎样在天黑前...
No, the real problem would be to get close to the Cambodian border

470
00:39:46,380 --> 00:39:47,840
通过柬埔寨边境
and back before dark.

471
00:39:48,007 --> 00:39:50,759
共军晚上控制了公路
The communists control that road at night.

472
00:39:50,926 --> 00:39:53,470
很多欧洲人在那儿被杀
So many Europeans have been killed out there.

473
00:40:04,773 --> 00:40:07,443
我是伦敦时报的托马斯.福勒
I am Thomas Fowler of the London Times

474
00:40:09,069 --> 00:40:12,531
我来这采访泰将军
and I'm here to interview General The.

475
00:40:15,034 --> 00:40:17,995
我是伦敦时报的托马斯.福勒
I'm Thomas Fowler of the London Times.

476
00:40:18,162 --> 00:40:21,957
我来这采访泰将军
I'm here to see General The.

477
00:40:31,216 --> 00:40:35,137
九月,十月,十一月...
September, October, November...

478
00:40:35,304 --> 00:40:38,807
派尔向凤未婚后我只见过他一次
I'd seen Pyle only once since he'd asked Phuong to marry him,

479
00:40:38,974 --> 00:40:40,934
在欧洲旅馆
at the Continental.

480
00:40:41,560 --> 00:40:42,978
当然,他很客气 -
He'd been polite, of course -

481
00:40:43,145 --> 00:40:46,273
问我怎样,凤怎样?
how was I, how was Phuong?

482
00:40:46,440 --> 00:40:48,984
他说他很忙,不在城里
He'd been busy, he said, out of the city,

483
00:40:49,151 --> 00:40:52,029
在忙他的医疗计划
working on his medical programme.

484
00:40:52,196 --> 00:40:55,074
不过不知何故,我并不讶异见到他
Though somehow, I wasn't surprised to see him.

485
00:40:55,240 --> 00:40:59,161
我讶异的是我很高兴见到他
I was surprised to be pleased to see him.

486
00:40:59,328 --> 00:41:03,499
- 什么风把你吹到这儿来了? - 我想采访泰将军
- What brings you out to these parts? - I was hoping to interview the General.

487
00:41:03,666 --> 00:41:06,502
但他们不让我进去
But they've thrown me out of the place.

488
00:41:06,669 --> 00:41:10,547
- 你这次又有什么借口? - 这就像是对我们的测试
- What's your excuse this time? - This is like a test run for us.

489
00:41:10,714 --> 00:41:14,301
法国人,以他们典型的法国伤风 非常不合作
The French, in their typically French way, have been very uncooperative

490
00:41:14,468 --> 00:41:18,764
但泰将军却不错 让我们在这儿扎营
but General The has been good enough to let us set up camp here.

491
00:41:19,181 --> 00:41:21,183
我让他们放你进去
I'll get them to let you in.

492
00:41:22,017 --> 00:41:25,896
乔.滕尼同与泰亲近的商人进行援助计划
Joe Tunney's running aid programmes with business people close to The.

493
00:41:26,063 --> 00:41:28,065
- 莫依先生 - 派乐先生
- Mr Muoi. - Mr Pyle.

494
00:41:29,483 --> 00:41:31,485
- 你好,你怎样? - 很好
- Hello. How are you? - Good.

495
00:41:51,839 --> 00:41:55,759
我姓莫依 泰将军只有几分钟时间
My name is Mr Muoi. The General only has a few moments.

496
00:41:55,884 --> 00:41:58,304
我能先问你一个问题吗?
May I first ask you a question?

497
00:41:58,470 --> 00:42:02,016
-请 - 你和泰将军是什么关系?
- Please. - What is your relationship to the General?

498
00:42:02,141 --> 00:42:04,810
我是生意人,也是爱国者
I'm a businessman and a patriot.

499
00:42:06,854 --> 00:42:11,358
你看到的这些供给和援助 很多都是我努力的结果
Many of the supplies and aid you see are the result of my efforts.

500
00:42:11,525 --> 00:42:13,319
可以开始了吗?
Shall we begin?

501
00:42:13,485 --> 00:42:15,446
你说你已脱离了
You say you've broken away from

502
00:42:15,612 --> 00:42:19,658
你所服役的法军和越军
the French and Vietnamese forces with which you serve.

503
00:42:19,825 --> 00:42:21,827
你们之间还有关系吗?
Do any ties remain?

504
00:42:26,123 --> 00:42:28,167
法国人是殖民主义者
The French are colonialists.

505
00:42:30,085 --> 00:42:32,087
不值得信任
Not to be trusted.

506
00:42:37,217 --> 00:42:40,846
应该由独立的越南人来管理这国家
It will take an independent Vietnamese leader to rule our country.

507
00:42:41,013 --> 00:42:44,308
只有这么少的供给和士兵
How does the General expect to launch a successful campaign

508
00:42:44,433 --> 00:42:47,436
将军你凭什么...
against the larger forces of the communists and the French

509
00:42:47,561 --> 00:42:49,730
打赢法军和共军大部队?
with so few men and supplies?

510
00:42:51,106 --> 00:42:55,152
谁为将军提供致胜手段?
And who is providing the means for the General to achieve this?

511
00:43:05,204 --> 00:43:07,498
他是否在北部作战?
Has he been fighting his war in the north?

512
00:43:24,848 --> 00:43:27,935
在Phat Diem有场大屠杀
There was a massacre at Phat Diem.

513
00:43:28,102 --> 00:43:29,812
你的军队是不是在那儿?
Were your forces present?

514
00:43:43,867 --> 00:43:48,455
很遗憾,将军突然想起有个紧急约见
Regrettably the General has just recalled that he has an urgent appointment.

515
00:43:48,622 --> 00:43:50,708
- 所以,请了 - 谢谢
- So, please. - Thank you.

516
00:44:03,512 --> 00:44:04,930
这么快
That was quick.

517
00:44:05,097 --> 00:44:08,726
事情不像我计划的那样
Things didn't go entirely according to plan.

518
00:44:08,851 --> 00:44:11,603
小心乔
Watch yourself with Joe.

519
00:44:11,770 --> 00:44:14,690
我觉得他和泰将军在搞鬼
I think he's up to something with General The.

520
00:44:16,942 --> 00:44:20,070
我能坐你的车回西贡吗? 我的车有点问题
Can I get a ride to Saigon with you? Something's wrong with my car.

521
00:44:20,237 --> 00:44:22,156
可以,当然可以
Yes, of course you can.

522
00:44:22,323 --> 00:44:26,744
看,有好心人帮我擦车
Hello. Some kind soul has had mine cleaned.

523
00:44:36,420 --> 00:44:39,673
我听说你将被召会伦敦
I heard a rumour that you'd been recalled to London.

524
00:44:40,382 --> 00:44:43,844
真的?谁告诉你的?
Really? Who told you that?

525
00:44:44,011 --> 00:44:46,972
凤的姐姐
Phuong's sister.

526
00:44:51,769 --> 00:44:54,521
- 妈的 - 怎么了?
- Shit. - What is it?

527
00:44:54,688 --> 00:44:57,274
没油了
We're out of petrol.

528
00:44:57,441 --> 00:45:00,653
刚才肯定有谁把油吸走了
Some bugger up in the mountains must have siphoned it off.

529
00:45:13,499 --> 00:45:16,335
也许他们在了望塔有备用油
They might have some spare petrol in that watchtower.

530
00:45:34,186 --> 00:45:36,855
看上去是废弃的塔
It looks like it's deserted.

531
00:45:36,981 --> 00:45:39,066
我进去看看
I'll go in and have a look.

532
00:45:48,325 --> 00:45:50,285
有人吗?
Hello?

533
00:46:17,938 --> 00:46:21,191
- 没事吧? - 上来
- Is everything OK? - Come up.

534
00:46:22,985 --> 00:46:27,823
我和我朋友不得不在这呆到早上了

535
00:46:31,910 --> 00:46:33,329
这是不允许的

536
00:46:34,621 --> 00:46:36,040
是我朋友

537
00:46:58,812 --> 00:47:01,774
没事的,请放下枪

538
00:47:01,774 --> 00:47:05,736
请放下枪,他是我朋友

539
00:47:30,219 --> 00:47:32,012
在想什么?
What are you thinking?

540
00:47:35,391 --> 00:47:38,602
在想凤现在在做什么
I was wondering what she was doing right now.

541
00:47:48,112 --> 00:47:51,073
今天早上她和朋友一起早茶
This morning she met her friends for elevenses

542
00:47:51,240 --> 00:47:53,575
在 La Fontaine.
at La Fontaine.

543
00:47:54,618 --> 00:47:57,079
吃冰淇淋,聊近来的闲话
Ice cream and the latest gossip.

544
00:47:59,331 --> 00:48:02,376
回家路上,她去了市集
On her way home she stopped at the market

545
00:48:02,543 --> 00:48:04,670
买鱼做午餐
for fresh fish for dinner.

546
00:48:06,630 --> 00:48:11,885
现在她在翻杂志
And now she's flipping through the pages of magazines

547
00:48:13,512 --> 00:48:16,515
看皇室成员和电影明星的照片
Iooking at photographs of the royal family and film stars,

548
00:48:19,018 --> 00:48:22,271
听巴赫的曲子
Iistening to Bach's Well-Tempered Clavier.

549
00:48:24,940 --> 00:48:27,401
我和她就是从巴赫开始的
I just got her started on Bach.

550
00:48:34,158 --> 00:48:36,410
你有过很多女人吗,托马斯?
Have you had a lot of women, Thomas?

551
00:48:39,455 --> 00:48:42,666
开始时很滥交
You start out by being promiscuous,

552
00:48:43,834 --> 00:48:46,503
但最后你会很专一 -
and end up like your grandfather -

553
00:48:46,628 --> 00:48:48,213
对一个女人忠诚不二
faithful to one woman.

554
00:48:50,341 --> 00:48:53,719
我知道凤不是没我就不行
I know I'm not essential to Phuong.

555
00:48:55,596 --> 00:48:58,307
但你相信我
But believe me when I tell you that

556
00:48:59,725 --> 00:49:01,644
如果我失去她
if I were to lose her,

557
00:49:03,854 --> 00:49:05,856
对我而言...
for me...

558
00:49:07,566 --> 00:49:10,235
就是死亡的开始
it would be the beginning of death.

559
00:49:19,370 --> 00:49:21,705
有人来了
Somebody's had it.

560
00:49:22,581 --> 00:49:26,335
从这到西贡有30或40个了望塔
There are 30 or 40 of these towers between here and Saigon.

561
00:49:26,502 --> 00:49:30,506
他们一晚只袭击一到两个 所以我们的机率不是很大
They only hit one or two a night so our odds aren't too bad.

562
00:49:33,133 --> 00:49:36,929
那你觉得共军来袭时他们会怎样?
So what do you think they'd do if the communists attacked?

563
00:49:37,096 --> 00:49:40,015
这两个人? 他们会开火然后逃跑
These two? They'd fire a shot and run.

564
00:49:40,933 --> 00:49:44,895
他们为什么要为我们而死? 或为法国人
Why should they die for us? Or the French.

565
00:49:45,813 --> 00:49:48,899
那是什么? 我看见有东西在动
What's that? I thought I saw something move.

566
00:49:55,698 --> 00:49:57,700
天啊,他们在这儿!
Christ, they're here!

567
00:50:02,913 --> 00:50:06,125
就我所听懂的 他们叫我们投降
As far as I can make out, he told them to give us up or else.

568
00:50:12,923 --> 00:50:15,342
别动! 给我枪!
Stop! Give me that!

569
00:50:15,509 --> 00:50:17,511
快来,托马斯
Come on, Thomas.

570
00:50:26,145 --> 00:50:28,480
- 怎么了? - 我想我扭到脚了
- What is it? - I think I've twisted my ankle.

571
00:51:11,857 --> 00:51:15,402
我沿路去下一个塔
I'm gonna head up the road to the next watchtower.

572
00:51:15,569 --> 00:51:19,239
看看能不能找到点汽油
See if I can find a French patrol.

573
00:51:19,948 --> 00:51:22,242
坐好,我会回来的
Sit tight, OK? I'll be back.

574
00:52:03,701 --> 00:52:06,537
能自我介绍吗?我叫托马斯. 福勒
May I introduce myself? Thomas Fowler.

575
00:52:26,890 --> 00:52:28,517
我找到汽油了
I found a patrol.

576
00:52:28,684 --> 00:52:30,978
如果我死了...
If I had died...

577
00:52:32,354 --> 00:52:34,898
你就能和她一起了
you could have had her.

578
00:52:44,533 --> 00:52:47,411
我想你得通知你的情报员
And I think you should inform your sources

579
00:52:47,578 --> 00:52:51,623
泰将军手下可不止他们所说的几百个人
that General The has a lot more men than the hundred of their count.

580
00:52:51,790 --> 00:52:54,585
我们得认真考虑他的报道
He's a story we should take seriously.

581
00:52:54,752 --> 00:52:57,129
别低估了爱国者,先生
Never underestimate a patriot, sir.

582
00:52:57,296 --> 00:53:01,675
你了解莫依吗? 他怎么能资助军队?
What do you know about Muoi? Could he finance The's army?

583
00:53:01,842 --> 00:53:04,094
他有家自行车厂!
He owns a bicycle factory!

584
00:53:04,261 --> 00:53:09,475
我想乔.滕尼和泰有阴谋
Well, I think Joe Tunney is plotting with he and The.

585
00:53:09,642 --> 00:53:12,311
他不止在搞外国援助这么简单
And it's more than just foreign aid programmes.

586
00:53:12,478 --> 00:53:15,189
我看看我能有什么消息,先生
I'll see what I can find out, sir.

587
00:53:20,152 --> 00:53:22,112
办公室一切都井井有条
Things are under control at the office.

588
00:53:22,279 --> 00:53:24,698
- 多休息休息吧 - 谢谢,辛
- Try to get some rest. - Thank you, Hinh.

589
00:53:58,816 --> 00:54:01,276
我好想你
I missed you.

590
00:54:01,443 --> 00:54:04,196
- 你还好吧? - 骨头还没散
- Are you all right? - I'm all in one piece.

591
00:54:04,363 --> 00:54:08,492
- 有封伦敦来的信 - 是吗?
- You got a letter from London. - Yes?

592
00:54:08,659 --> 00:54:11,996
- 我帮你拿? - 不,亲亲我
- I fetch it for you? - No. Give me a kiss.

593
00:54:12,788 --> 00:54:14,373
再亲
Big one.

594
00:54:18,460 --> 00:54:19,878
我来拿
I will get it.

595
00:54:30,139 --> 00:54:32,182
你看起来很害怕
You look afraid.

596
00:54:32,349 --> 00:54:35,853
我想我最好还是喝点白兰地
I think I'd better have a brandy and soda.

597
00:54:57,958 --> 00:55:00,336
派尔,进来,进来
Pyle. Come in, come in.

598
00:55:03,756 --> 00:55:06,133
我想顺便过来看看你怎样
Thought I'd drop by and see how you were doing.

599
00:55:06,300 --> 00:55:09,595
- 我很好,谢谢 - 腿怎样?
- Very well, thanks. - How's the leg?

600
00:55:09,762 --> 00:55:13,432
不能打网球了 不过我本来就不会打
My tennis game will suffer, but it wasn't much to begin with.

601
00:55:17,311 --> 00:55:18,354
谢谢
Thank you.

602
00:55:18,520 --> 00:55:20,648
我很高兴你能来
I'm glad you dropped by.

603
00:55:20,814 --> 00:55:24,777
我们得谢谢派尔先生 他救了我的命
We have to thank Mr Pyle, Phuong, for saving my life.

604
00:55:28,989 --> 00:55:30,407
谢谢
Thank you.

605
00:55:30,574 --> 00:55:32,326
你姐姐怎样?
How's your sister doing?

606
00:55:32,493 --> 00:55:34,244
- 姐姐? - 是的
- Sister? - Yes.

607
00:55:34,411 --> 00:55:38,123
艾登为她找了份工作,为美国人做事
Alden got her a job with Americans.

608
00:55:38,290 --> 00:55:39,708
噢,是吗?
Oh, yes?

609
00:55:39,875 --> 00:55:42,586
她很喜欢那工作,谢谢
She likes it very much. Thank you.

610
00:55:42,753 --> 00:55:45,005
好的,我很高兴
Good. I'm very glad.

611
00:55:45,172 --> 00:55:48,050
既然你们俩都在这儿
Since you're both here, now is as good a time as any

612
00:55:48,217 --> 00:55:52,596
我收到我妻子的信
to tell you that I have received a letter from my wife

613
00:55:53,639 --> 00:55:56,350
她同意和我离婚了
and she has more or less agreed to give me a divorce.

614
00:56:02,690 --> 00:56:05,067
那太好了
That's wonderful.

615
00:56:09,780 --> 00:56:13,993
- 过来坐 - 谢谢,我还有事儿
- Come sit. - Thank you. I've got plans.

616
00:56:14,159 --> 00:56:15,995
感谢到访
Thank you for dropping by.

617
00:56:18,205 --> 00:56:20,040
再见
Bye.

618
00:56:39,184 --> 00:56:40,894
先生,我...
Sir, l...

619
00:56:44,481 --> 00:56:46,900
我信任你,托马斯
I trusted you, Thomas.

620
00:56:47,943 --> 00:56:50,988
有女人在就有麻烦
Always a mistake when there's a woman involved.

621
00:56:51,155 --> 00:56:53,115
你不用谎言就不可能赢我?
Couldn't you have won without lying?

622
00:56:54,325 --> 00:56:55,909
怎么了,到底?
What is it, anyway?

623
00:56:56,076 --> 00:56:58,662
我姐姐看了你妻子的信
My sister read the letter from your wife.

624
00:56:58,829 --> 00:57:00,998
我给她看的
I show it to her

625
00:57:01,165 --> 00:57:05,753
因为...我太自豪了
because... I was so proud.

626
00:57:05,919 --> 00:57:09,089
- 太高兴了 - 你怎么能这样欺骗她?
- So happy. - How could you treat her like this?

627
00:57:13,469 --> 00:57:16,138
''亲爱的托马斯- 你身边总是有女人
"Dear Thomas - you always picked up women

628
00:57:16,263 --> 00:57:18,432
就像你的鞋总粘到泥一样''
Iike you picked up mud on your shoes."

629
00:57:18,599 --> 00:57:21,143
我很抱歉,凤
I'm sorry, Phuong.

630
00:57:21,310 --> 00:57:24,772
- 那你为什么要骗她? - 很明显因为我想留住她
- So then why'd you lie to her? - Because I wanted to keep her.

631
00:57:24,938 --> 00:57:26,649
那不是爱
That's not love.

632
00:57:27,733 --> 00:57:29,485
看到吧,他甚至都不否认自己是个骗子

633
00:57:31,570 --> 00:57:36,283
''你难道没想过当你离开她回英国她会有多寂寞吗?''
"Have you ever stopped to think how lonely she'll be in England when you leave her?"

634
00:57:36,450 --> 00:57:38,452
闭嘴,看在老天的份上
Shut up, for Christ's sake.

635
00:57:40,579 --> 00:57:42,998
''我不主张离婚''
"l don't believe in divorce."

636
00:57:43,165 --> 00:57:48,087
''我的信仰也不允许 因此答案还是
"My religion forbids it. And so the answer is

637
00:57:48,253 --> 00:57:49,713
不.''
no."

638
00:57:52,174 --> 00:57:55,219
我被教育别看人家的信
I was taught never to read other people's letters.

639
00:57:55,386 --> 00:57:58,597
- 我被教育别说谎 - 走吧,凤
- I was taught not to tell lies. - Come on, Phuong.

640
00:58:01,600 --> 00:58:03,686
我不说越南话
I don't speak Vietnamese.

641
00:58:05,145 --> 00:58:06,855
滚吧
Get lost.

642
00:58:14,071 --> 00:58:17,199
你是对的,莫依的确有关系网
You were right about Muoi. He does have connections.

643
00:58:17,366 --> 00:58:19,660
呆会再谈这个好吗?
Can we discuss this some other time?

644
00:58:19,827 --> 00:58:22,663
外国板条箱通过他的厂进来
Crates from overseas have been moving through his factory,

645
00:58:22,830 --> 00:58:24,957
绕过法国海关
bypassing French customs.

646
00:58:25,124 --> 00:58:28,252
我的情报员不知道箱里装的是什么
My sources have been unable to determine what they contain.

647
00:58:30,295 --> 00:58:32,840
他很可能贿赂了什么人
He's probably got someone on the take.

648
00:58:33,590 --> 00:58:35,551
他是出口商,不是进口商
He's an exporter, not an importer.

649
00:58:35,718 --> 00:58:38,804
好的,我们明天再查好吗?
Yes, well, we'll do that tomorrow, OK?

650
00:58:38,971 --> 00:58:41,515
不,今天下午就要出货了
No. A shipment just came in this afternoon.

651
00:58:41,682 --> 00:58:43,934
明早就运走了
It could be gone by the morning.

652
01:00:11,605 --> 01:00:14,566
- Diolacton是什么? - 我们得马上走
- What is this Diolacton? - We must leave immediately.

653
01:00:15,275 --> 01:00:17,361
这英国人疯了,他喝太多了

654
01:00:17,361 --> 01:00:18,654
回家去吧,回家

655
01:00:18,654 --> 01:00:21,407
他什么也不是

656
01:00:21,782 --> 01:00:24,660
- 你在干什么? - 在救你的命,快走!
- What are you doing? - Trying to save your life. Go!

657
01:01:07,161 --> 01:01:08,120
早上好
Good morning.

658
01:01:08,287 --> 01:01:10,956
- 我能为你做什么? -你已经做了够多了
- Can I help you? - You've done quite enough already.

659
01:01:12,750 --> 01:01:16,920
- 派尔在哪? - 他今天上午不在这
- Where's Pyle? - He's not in the office this morning.

660
01:01:17,087 --> 01:01:19,882
- 他很多事在家做 - 我知道他在家做什么
- He does a lot of work at home. - I know what he does at home.

661
01:01:20,049 --> 01:01:23,844
- 你什么意思? - 问她,她把我的女人和他配了队
- What do you mean? - Ask her. She's fixed him up with my girl.

662
01:01:24,011 --> 01:01:26,889
- 你不能在办公室生事 -  我知道这样很粗鲁
- We can't have scenes in the office. - I know I am behaving badly.

663
01:01:27,056 --> 01:01:29,475
但我有充分理由粗鲁
But I have every intention of behaving badly.

664
01:01:29,642 --> 01:01:33,979
谁在这种情况下都会发火
This is exactly the kind of situation where one should behave badly.

665
01:01:34,146 --> 01:01:37,024
- 你能声音小一点吗? -  你干嘛不滚开?
- Could we please lower our voices? - Why don't you bugger off?

666
01:01:37,191 --> 01:01:39,026
托马斯,这儿有女士
Thomas, there is a lady here.

667
01:01:39,193 --> 01:01:41,362
我和这个女士很熟
This lady and I know each other quite well.

668
01:01:41,528 --> 01:01:44,823
她本来想从我身上捞油水 现在她从派尔那捞
She tried to get a rake-off from me, but now she's getting one from Pyle.

669
01:01:44,990 --> 01:01:48,410
- 我们有很多事要做 -  如果派尔打电话来,跟他说我来过
- We have a lot of work to do. - If Pyle phones, tell him I called.

670
01:01:48,577 --> 01:01:51,455
他应该回访
It would be polite to return the visit.

671
01:01:55,250 --> 01:01:56,794
他怎么进来的?
How did he get in here?

672
01:02:35,249 --> 01:02:37,001
这是波士顿吗?
This is Boston?

673
01:02:37,167 --> 01:02:40,879
不,这是尼加拉瀑布.这也是
No, that's Niagara Falls. So is that.

674
01:02:42,673 --> 01:02:45,551
这是波士顿,那是法纳尔大厅
This is Boston. That's Faneuil Hall.

675
01:02:48,137 --> 01:02:50,472
我等不及想带你回祖国
I can't wait to take you to my country.

676
01:03:01,567 --> 01:03:04,111
我学校里的朋友
My friend from school.

677
01:03:05,195 --> 01:03:08,615
她和男友去机场
She go to airport with her boyfriend.

678
01:03:10,451 --> 01:03:13,787
他说要带她去法国
He said he'd take her to France.

679
01:03:19,168 --> 01:03:21,253
但在机场
But in the airport,

680
01:03:21,420 --> 01:03:25,507
他不见了,留她一人在那儿
he disappear, leave her there.

681
01:03:26,425 --> 01:03:29,386
很多交了法国男友的女孩
So many girls with French boyfriend,

682
01:03:31,680 --> 01:03:34,433
没一个嫁过去
no one to marry them.

683
01:03:36,060 --> 01:03:38,020
我不会那样对你
Well, that'll never happen to you.

684
01:03:52,951 --> 01:03:55,371
我保证
I promise.

685
01:04:06,965 --> 01:04:09,760
- 嗨 - 圣诞节过得好吗?
- Hi. - Have a nice Christmas?

686
01:04:09,927 --> 01:04:12,054
有派队
One long party.

687
01:04:12,221 --> 01:04:14,515
凤忘了什么吗?
Did Phuong forget something?

688
01:04:14,682 --> 01:04:17,059
听说你来过公使馆
Heard you came by the legation.

689
01:04:17,226 --> 01:04:19,019
是的
Yes.

690
01:04:19,186 --> 01:04:21,981
- 那是谁? - 保镖.我们现在都有保镖
- Who's this? - Bodyguard. We all have them now.

691
